Beyond the Glam

At Miss Universe India, beauty takes centre stage but what most don’t see is what happens before the spotlight hits. That’s where Pooja Lalwani Tamang came in.

As The Lipstick Diary and the founder of Fit Face, she was invited to speak to the contestants about something far more crucial than beauty: skin prep as a ritual, not a step.

From daily face massages to deep hydration habits, Pooja broke down the art of glowing skin that lasts beyond pageants and photo-ops.

Her message was simple but powerful: great makeup begins where great skin lives. And with her signature mix of beauty science, real talk, and rituals that actually work, she left the room not just inspired but informed.

Because in the world of crowns, the real win is confidence that’s skin-deep.
